(I appreciate the "cross word" pun though - I actually might not mind a puzzle themed around it)

@Andrzej

I agree with Jennie’s thought. If you want constant action and a lot of scoring, and you go to a baseball game, you might be disappointed. Instead of complaining about the nature of baseball, you should go to a basketball game instead. 

Baseball is a great game for other reasons. But it might not be for everyone.

@Andrzej

Puns are common in crosswords, as are low scoring and a slow pace is in baseball.  If you engage in either activity, you shouldn’t be surprised to find they are the way they are. 

Surely this is not the first time—or the 91st—time you’ve solved a puzzle with a punny theme?

@Steve L

Who says I'm surprised? I'm not. But since most themed puzzles are not punny, I continue to do them. You might remember I skip Kugelman puzzles - because they are always dad-joke-fests.

Should I stop going for hikes because occasionally the route turns out to be unenjoyable?

